  "summary": "While rowing on a lake, Anthony Kidd questions Bandel about her French tutor, Jeanne Viel. Bandel explains she hired Viel through an agency for a hundred pounds a year. Viel previously lived for ten years at the Chateau de Briodulle in Digne, France, in the house of the Comtesse de Briodulle. Anthony notes that Bandel has only corresponded with the Countess by letter and has never met her, which seems to satisfy his inquiry.\n\nDuring their conversation, Bandel discusses the chimney house, noting that while it has historical significance, it is often used for boring tourist tours led by Mr. Tredwell. Anthony observes a melancholy man by the boathouse, whom Bandel identifies as Bill. After Bandel goes to meet Bill, Anthony plays \"Indian\" with two children, Giggles and Shimmer. Following the game, Anthony notices a black-bearded stranger hurrying across the courtyard. He then encounters Mr. Fitch, who appears flushed and out of breath, as if he had been running.\n\nChief Constable Bartle appears suddenly, and Anthony subsequently requests permission from Sheriff Balthazar to travel to the Chateau de Briodulle in Digne, France. Anthony plans to depart after tomorrow's autopsy and return by Sunday evening. The Sheriff grants permission on the condition that Anthony returns directly. Anthony expresses his suspicion that a specific memoir is the central cause of the ongoing troubles.",
